MTHATHA - South Africa joins the world in marking World Aids Day on Friday, 1 December.  The country's main commemorative event took place in the Eastern Cape with HealthMinisterr Aaron Motsoaledi and the premier of the Eastern Cape Premier, Phumulo Masualle in attendance.  Deputy President, Cyril Ramaphosa will met with traditional leaders ahead of the official event. Ramaphosa said traditional leaders have an important role to play in the fight against HIV and Aids. "You, as our traditional leaders are the custodians of our customs and traditions of our people. You are the of all the norms, the standards, and behavioural attitudes of our people. And our people hold you in high regard because you are the standard bearers," said Ramaphosa.  eNCA